<TEXT>
the oakland athletics showing the 
pitching and power that made them baseballs winningest team 
dismissed the san francisco giants 50 saturday night in the world 
series opener 
dave stewart pitched a fivehitter for his third postseason 
victory this year he walked one and struck out six 
oakland roughed up national league earned run average leader 
scott garrelts for five runs in four innings 
dave parker and walt weiss each homered and the athletics 
finished with 11 hits including three by mark mcgwire 
rickey henderson the most valuable player in the american 
league playoffs went 2for5 with a runscoring single but did not 
steal a base after swiping a record eight in the playoffs will 
clark the national league playoff mvp went 2for4 
stewart throwing 95 mph fastballs at twilight had trouble only 
on balls hit back to him 
stewart made a twobase throwing error on robby thompsons 
comebacker in the first inning in the third jose uribe got an 
infield hit when stewart failed to cleanly catch the ball and threw 
a shade late to first base 
dave henderson walked on five pitches to start the second and 
oneout singles by terry steinbach and tony phillips made it 10 
with runners at first and third weiss nubbed a slow grounder to 
first that clark fielded doublepumped and threw home to terry 
kennedy steinbach however kicked the ball loose from his rival 
catchers mitt for an error and was safe 
rickey henderson singled home another run for a 30 lead 
parker homered to open the third and weiss homered to lead off 
the fourth 
