<TEXT>
violent thunderstorms ripped across upstate 
new york saturday with heavy rain hail and wind up to 85 mph 
knocking out power to thousands of homes and killing at least one 
person 
a man was killed and three other people including two boys 
were slightly injured when their mobile home was blown several 
hundred feet from its foundation in mcdonough police said 
a canfield ohio man escaped injury when a gust of wind blew 
his singleengine cessna aircraft onto its side as he was preparing 
for takeoff from niagara falls international airport police said 
a sky diver who was aloft when the storm hit was yanked upward 
1500 feet in three seconds said niagara county sheriffs deputy 
duane jacobs 
the parachutist david konstabel 32 of west seneca told 
police that when he hit the ground he was dragged 300 feet across 
a barbedwire fence and into some trees in the town of newfane 
konstabel was reported in stable condition with injuries to his 
right leg in erie county medical center in buffalo 
after konstabel began ascending he cut his main parachute away 
and descended using his reserve chute said henry szczepanski 
skydiving instructor for konstabels group 
this thing just came across the lake and whacked us 
szczepanski said of the storm 
thousands of homes were left without electricity when power 
lines were downed from the niagara frontier to the vermont state 
line 
winds reached as much as 85 mph in ithaca and in nearby lansing 
the roof was blown off an apartment building said tompkins county 
sheriffs dispatcher julie morehouse 
two people were hurt 
</TEXT>
