<TEXT>
the federal reserve is ready to move large 
amounts of cash into the american banking system on monday if the 
money is needed to prevent a financial crisis sparked by a sharp 
drop in stock prices it was reported sunday 
flooding the banking system with money could reduce the risk 
that fridays 190point fall in the dow jones average will turn 
into a more serious financial disaster on monday the washington 
post and the new york times reported 
markets will be able to count on us to make sure the financial 
system stays fluid the times quoted an unidentified official of 
the federal reserve board as saying 
on monday it should be quite evident to the market that we 
will satisfy liquidity needs our action in the market should make 
it clear an unnamed fed official told the post liquidity refers 
to the ready availability of cash 
the feds promise is aimed at preventing a repeat of the wall 
street situation two years ago when the market fell 508 points in 
a single day 
on the day before that fall the stock index had fallen 108 
points leading mutual fund shareholders to cash in their shares 
as the mutual funds ran low they had to sell more shares to raise 
money which in turn caused stock prices to drop even lower 
to calm the markets its important that institutions know 
there are adequate funds available the official told the times 
once the markets realize there will be no credit crunch we can 
resume normal business 
according to the unnamed official quoted by the times the feds 
decision was taken at a meeting late friday and was being 
