<TEXT>
a top secret government program known as the 
doomsday project is leaving a bitter legacy with a veteran 
counterintelligence expert alleging he is being harassed for 
reporting improprieties and poor management 
the program referred to at the pentagon simply as project 908 
is designed to ensure that even if top us civilian leaders are 
killed in a surprise nuclear attack the united states can still 
unleash its own atomic weapons on the soviet union 
so far the government has spent 4 billion to 5 billion to 
build supply depots underground bunkers and a communications 
network that has been plagued with problems say pentagon sources 
speaking on condition of anonymity 
the army inspector generals office reviewed the program in 1987 
and interviewed army civilian employee w thomas golden 
golden chief of the operations security branch at the 
information systems command in fort huachuca ariz asserted to 
the ig that 
the communications network vital to the project didnt work 
properly was costing hundreds of millions of dollars to fix and 
project 908 officials on several occasions misled members of 
congress into believing that the system was operational when in 
fact it wasnt 
the son of army brig gen eugene renzi was doing work for 
betac corp an arlington va firm to which renzi had directed a 
solesource nobid contract in connection with project 908 
the betac contract specified that one of renzis aides would be 
a 400aday consultant to the company 
army regulations say the inspector general will protect the 
anonymity of witnesses but within weeks of goldens confidential 
discussions word had leaked to renzi that golden was making 
allegations against the general 
golden alleged that col ned bacheldor chief of the inspector 
generals intelligence oversight division had informed renzi that 
golden was the source of the allegation about renzis son renzi 
told army investigators in sworn testimony he had found out about 
goldens allegations from an aide not from bacheldor 
the army inspector generals office concluded that renzi had 
retaliated against golden by spreading word that golden would not 
be welcome at fort ritchie md where renzi directed the 7th 
signal command 
because of renzis action goldens effectiveness was 
diminished and he could not do his job according to an army 
memo obtained by the associated press 
golden requested reassignment and now handles 
counterintelligence matters in connection with the strategic 
defense initiative 
renzi was reprimanded for retaliating against golden but has 
since been promoted to the rank of major general and is stationed 
in hawaii 
renzi bacheldor and golden all rejected interview requests made 
through military spokesmen 
but the ap has learned that renzi told a house armed services 
committee investigator late last year that bacheldor had leaked 
goldens name to renzis boss lt gen emmett paige who passed it 
along to renzi 
