<TEXT>
the education department is expanding the 
scope of its regional strategy sessions to include initiatives 
beyond choice after months of wrangling with the chairman of 
the house education committee about the meetings limited agenda 
education secretary lauro cavazos opens the first session monday 
night when he meets with east harlem ny parents a daylong 
session complete with a plenary and concurrent workshops will 
follow on tuesday 
our purpose in calling for these meetings is to ratchet up the 
debate about the importance of choice in the move to restructure 
schools said education undersecretary john sanders 
choice is the concept that allows parents to decide where their 
children will attend school it is based on the theory that 
competition will shake up and improve bad schools 
however rep augustus hawkins chairman of the house education 
and labor committee had argued that the education departments 
strategy sessions should address other proposals for education 
reform 
hawkins said he and several committee members object to 
choice because we believe its a new way of resegregating the 
schools he added that some disadvantaged children also may be 
forced to give up needed services in order to attend a school 
outside the district 
