the new law reauthorizes virtually all major federal elementary 
and secondary education programs through fiscal year 1993 
including chapter one for the disadvantaged science and math 
programs magnet programs for specialized instruction bilingual 
education and child development 
hawkins said the new law provided for some accountability at 
school districts to document improvements over each year as well 
as local control 
