company in the netherlands displayed his deepfrozen machine 
that sells a consumer a frozen dinner and has a builtin microwave 
oven to heat it up 
to make it easier for customers to pay for these items vendors 
are moving toward introducing debit card systems especially on 
college campuses stone said 
customers can feed bills such as 10 into a machine which 
produces a magneticstrip credit card when the card is inserted 
into a vending machine to buy an item like a 50cent candy bar the 
purchase price is automatically deducted leaving 950 on the card 
